# 2033. Minimum Operations to Make a Uni-Value Grid

**Difficulty:** Medium
**Topic:** Array, Math, Sorting
**Date:** April 2026
**Status:** ✅ Solved

---

## Problem Summary
2D grid diya hai aur ek integer x. Ek operation mein kisi bhi
element mein x add ya subtract kar sakte ho.
Minimum operations return karo jisse saare elements equal ho jayein.
Agar possible nahi hai toh -1 return karo.

---

## Key Observations

### 1. Kab impossible hai?
Agar kisi bhi do elements ka remainder (% x) alag hai toh
unhe kabhi equal nahi bana sakte.
```
grid = [[3,1,2]], x = 2
3%2=1, 1%2=1, 2%2=0 → alag remainder → return -1
```

### 2. Kaunsi value pe sabko laayein? → MEDIAN
Median pe laane se minimum operations lagte hain.
Mean use nahi kar sakte kyunki elements integers rehne chahiye.

### 3. Operations count
```
operations = abs(element - median) / x
```

---

## Approach
1. Grid flatten karo ek 1D array mein
2. Remainder check karo — alag hai toh -1
3. Array sort karo
4. Median nikalo → arr[size/2]
5. Har element ke liye abs(ele - median) / x add karo

---

## Bugs I Faced 🐛

### Bug 1 — Flatten loop galat tha
```cpp
// ❌ Wrong
for(auto ele : grid){
    arr[ele] = grid[ele][ele]; // ele ek row(vector) hai, number nahi!
}

// ✅ Fixed
int idx = 0;
for(int i = 0; i < m; i++)
    for(int j = 0; j < n; j++)
        arr[idx++] = grid[i][j];
```

### Bug 2 — Remainder check sirf m tak tha (main bug!)
```cpp
// ❌ Wrong — m=1 tha toh sirf 1 element check hua!
for(int i = 0; i < m; i++)
    if(arr[i] % x != rem) return -1;

// ✅ Fixed — poora array check karo
for(auto ele : arr)
    if(ele % x != rem) return -1;
```

### Bug 3 — Operations accumulate nahi ho rahi thi
```cpp
// ❌ Wrong
int op;                        // initialize nahi kiya
op = (ele - median) / x;      // += nahi, overwrite ho raha tha

// ✅ Fixed
int op = 0;
op += abs((ele - median) / x); // abs() aur += dono zaroori!
```

---

## What I Learned
- 2D grid flatten karte waqt loop hamesha `m*n` tak hona chahiye
- `auto ele : grid` mein ele poori row hoti hai, element nahi
- Accumulate karna ho toh `+=` use karo, `=` nahi
- Variables hamesha initialize karo (`int op = 0`)
- Median minimum absolute deviation deta hai — isliye mean nahi

---

## Solution

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int x) {
        int m = grid.size();
        int n = grid[0].size();
        vector<int> arr(m * n);
        int indx = 0;
        
        for(int i = 0; i < m; i++)
            for(int j = 0; j < n; j++)
                arr[indx++] = grid[i][j];
        
        int rem = arr[0] % x;
        for(auto ele : arr)
            if(ele % x != rem)
                return -1;
        
        sort(arr.begin(), arr.end());
        int median = arr[arr.size() / 2];
        
        int op = 0;
        for(auto ele : arr)
            op += abs((ele - median) / x);
        
        return op;
    }
};
```

---

## Complexity
- **Time:** O(m×n log m×n) — sorting ki wajah se
- **Space:** O(m×n) — flatten array

